<TITLE> Seaports on alert as cyclone moves over Bay </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 12 (bdnews24.com)The maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla were advised to hoist distant warning signal two as a cyclone hovered over the Bay of Bengal on Saturday. Cyclone 'Ward', developing over the southwest and adjoining southeast Bay of Bengal, moved slightly northwestward through the day. It was centred about 1615 kilometres south-southwest of Chittagong port, 1,545 kms south-southwest of Cox's Bazar port and 1,505 kms south-southwest of Mongla port at 10pm, said a Met Department bulletin. It is likely to intensify further moving in a northwesterly direction, said the bulletin. Maximum sustained wind speed within 54 kms of the storm centre was about 60 kph rising to 80 kph in gusts/ squalls. The sea will remain rough near the storm, warned the weather office. All fishing boats and trawlers over the north Bay and deep sea were advised to remain close to the coast and proceed with caution till further notice.
